FBIS4-16791 "drsov076_b_94039" FBIS-SOV-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Chernomyrdin Notes `Complex Conditions' for Navy Chernomyrdin Notes `Complex Conditions' for Navy PM1904144694 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 19 Apr 94 p 1 PM1904144694 Moscow PRAVDA Russian BFN [PRAVDA and ITAR-TASS column report under the rubric "In Brief": "Enemies All Around"] [Text] "The task of building a new Russian Navy has to be resolved in extremely complex conditions. All the negative processes taking place in the Russian economy are also having an effect on service. We have lost a number of military bases in the Baltic, Black, and Caspian Seas, and attempts to play the naval card are continuing in various political circles," Viktor Chernomyrdin, Russian Federation Government prime minister, stated on Sunday, taking part in the ceremony of the commissioning in the Russian Navy of the first category destroyer Besstrashnyy.
